reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Perfect for my needs. Easy to use and perfect for traveling. There are even extra fuses for added reliability. Super portable and reliable, it's a one-stop charging station when traveling. Takes up almost no space but is very efficient.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Well made, compact converter
reviews.reviewText: Like the compact size, versatility and reasonable price. Worked fine on a recent overseas trip.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars curling iron melted
reviews.reviewText: This converter/adapter did not step down 220 to 110 (yes, the switch was flipped). The handle on the curling iron warmed & started to melt almost immediately in Paris (Europe), and then again in London (UK). It works fine for charging devices (USB) but NOT for actually stepping down 220 to 110. Many hotel rooms have at least 1 USB port, so you don't need it for that unless you need multiple USBs for charging multiple devices. We had another converter/adapter that worked perfectly which leads me to think you have to spend about $60 to get a good one for curling irons.
